The '''Assertion Definition Language''' ('''ADL''') is a [[specification language]] providing a formal grammar to specify behaviour and interfaces for computer [[software]].<ref name="About ADL.">http://adl.opengroup.org/about/index.html</ref> ADL uses function [[Precondition|pre-]] and [[postcondition]]s to specify interfaces and is designed to provide an intermediary between informal English language specifications and formal programmatic test specifications. Tool support exists both to convert ADL specifications into natural language, and to generate test systems against which implementation code can be verified.<ref name="About ADL." />

ADL is developed cooperatively by [[The Open Group]] and [[SunTest]] of [[Sun Microsystems]] <ref name="About ADL: History.">http://adl.opengroup.org/about/history.html</ref>

